column5: I relate to this a lot, not entirely sure if it is normal but I do the same so there's at least two of us my friend

My mum accidentally tagged me in a rant about how annoying my brother and I are to have around the house even though we don't really impact her life too much by being home (I'm 16 and am homeschooling, so I'm in my room for 14+ hours a day and same with my 11 year old brother) like I'm sorry you don't see us anyway the only inconvenience to her is that we might eat a bit more food from home bc we don't have the option of buying stuff from the tuck shop at school like Hshdbdhdhdh it frustrates me bc she's even admitted that she has no idea what to do with us bc she's trained in early childhood so after the age of 6 she was making it us as he goes which is fine but fuck surely someone with enough knowledge to know that if you talk down to a child, they get sad, maybe, just maybe, if you treat me like I'm below you I might just fall into depression, just like a 3 year old. Like ffs man I'm sorry I'm depressed and not performing the best in school maybe I'm fucking freaking out bc I don't even know wether I can graduate next year!!! Just fuck honestly just fuck
